A 30-year-old woman, Elizabeth Ibezim has been arraigned before an Ikeja Chief Magistrate Court for allegedly stealing a two-year-old girl in a market. Prosecuting Inspector Benson Emeurhi told the court on Monday that Elizabeth committed the offence May 22 at Mile 12 market area of Lagos. Benson informed the court that the defendant was caught with a two-year-old Ramadanat Mutinu around 10.30am in the market Elizabeth pleaded not guilty. Chief Magistrate Olufunke Sule-Amzat granted the defendant N100,000 bail with two sureties in the like sum. She ordered the addresses of the sureties to be verified. She adjourned the case till July 9.